  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He threw them to the-- to the-- to the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one of them escaped from a train-- on a prisoners train, he escaped from the train.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Palgi and Goldstein, who was-- who used to play football against each other-- he was from [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then somehow they were able to escape in a mishmash somehow, and I wanted to speak to him, because he was the closest to-- closest to Hannah.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I wanted to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But mind you, I was warned by this communist there, and-- and-- and-- and in-- in-- in-- in Budapest by [INAUDIBLE], where the way the situation, the [?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Haganah, ?] he get hold of you and you never, never returned from it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then the situation was so bad there-- a bunch of mad men.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And some of them, mind you, were British trained, in the same service, and and then-- then they joined the Haganah, and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But also, this one who landed in Toronto, they told me-- we looked.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Your kind of stories, they're so nationalist, so Zionist and so extremist.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so when you learned [INAUDIBLE] that this kind of story-- and oh, when I came back after that radio, television interview, two weeks later, I had a telephone call from the Jewish Defense League here-- here in Canada, right on the telephone there, and they-- they threatened me.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I told them, all right, come, you son of a bitch [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Who-- where you are and what I am, and my story is what I, what I-- I told to Hungary and to the world, whoever wants to know it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I'm not going to back down.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But you want to meet me?",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
